# Root_Project

Python CLI-first implementation of the board game Root, designed so a GUI can be added with minimal refactoring.

## Current Scope

- CLI gameplay loop with legal action listing and turn progression
- Core game state models for map, factions, cards, phases, and scoring
- Rules engine with movement, battle, crafting, draw/discard, sympathy spread, and victory checks
- Faction phase hooks for Marquise, Eyrie, Woodland Alliance, and Vagabond
- Save/load snapshot utilities

## Project Layout

- `src/root_game/domain`: Rules and immutable/structured game models
- `src/root_game/application`: Game service and turn orchestration API
- `src/root_game/interfaces/cli`: Command-line adapter
- `src/root_game/interfaces/gui`: GUI integration contracts (placeholder interfaces)
- `src/root_game/infrastructure`: Persistence and utilities
- `tests`: Domain, application, and interface tests

## Setup

```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -e .[dev]
```

## Run

```bash
python -m root_game.main
```

## Test

```bash
pytest
```

## Coverage Roadmap

- Add deeper faction-specific rule tests (decree, outrage, crafting edge cases)
- Add integration tests that replay deterministic full games with fixed seeds
- Add contract tests for future GUI adapter using `interfaces/gui/contracts.py`
